  <div class="friendReviews elementListBrown" >
    <div class="section">
      

<div id="review_2043604545" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/2043604545" />
    <a title="Teresita" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/43974266-teresita"><img alt="Teresita" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1477274104p2/43974266.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/2043604545?book_show_action=true">Jan 27, 2018</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Teresita" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Teresita" href="/user/show/43974266-teresita">Teresita</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Kindle Edition " href="/book/show/25105319-serving-crazy-with-curry">review of another edition</a>


        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2043604545" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer11191230942006107918">Nice book, it isn&apos;t a page turner type of book. Explores the aftermath of what a suicide attempt does to a family. Discusses the complexities of marriage, love, and relationships within a family. Also uses food in an interesting way to bring family closer together. Second book I&apos;ve read by this author, will probably read some more of her stuff.</span>
  <span id="freeText11191230942006107918" style="display:none">Nice book, it isn't a page turner type of book. Explores the aftermath of what a suicide attempt does to a family. Discusses the complexities of marriage, love, and relationships within a family. Also uses food in an interesting way to bring family closer together. Second book I've read by this author, will probably read some more of her stuff.</span>
  <a data-text-id="11191230942006107918" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
